50|$|Starting in 2003, {{the center}} has taken part in a program to {{reintroduce}} the <b>wood</b> <b>bison</b> back into Alaska after a 100-year absence. The <b>wood</b> <b>bison</b> is the largest land mammal in North America, and is a keystone grazing herbivore from the region. The first release date is scheduled for 2011. This project is a joint effort with the Alaska Department of Fish & Game and other conservation groups.|$|E
